 argues, are more effective than policing, juvenile courts, or incarceration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aDélinquance juvénilexAspect socialxÉtats-UnisxUnited States. 0aDélinquance juvénilexPréventionxÉtats-Unis. 0aJeunes délinquantsxRééducationxÉtats-Unis. 0aJeunes délinquantsxSanté mentale. 0aJuvenile delinquencyxPreventionxUnited States. 0aJuvenile delinquencyxSocial aspectsxUnited States. 0aJuvenile delinquencyxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aJuvenile delinquencyzUnited StatesxPrevention. 0aJuvenile delinquentsxMental health. 0aJuvenile delinquentsxRehabilitationxUnited States. 0aJuvenile delinquentsxRehabilitationzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300127775423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300127775.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles